"Community association" means a Maryland nonprofit association, corporation, or other organization that is located exclusively in an area of the county that is outside of a municipal corporation and:
Is comprised of at least 25% of adult residents of a local community consisting of 40 or more individual, contiguous households as defined by specific geographic boundaries in the bylaws or charter of the association;
Requires, as a condition of membership, the voluntary payment of monetary dues at least annually;
Is operated primarily for the promotion of social welfare and general neighborhood improvement and enhancement;
Has been in existence for at least 2 years when it files suit under this section;
Is exempt from taxation under § 501(c)(3) or (4) of the Internal Revenue Code; and
In the case of a Maryland corporation, is in good standing.

"Local code violation" means a violation under the following provisions of the Prince George's County Code as amended from time to time or under any applicable code relating to the following provisions incorporated into the Prince George's County Code by reference:
Animal control regulations (§ 3-131 et seq.) and other rules, regulations, and standards (§ 3-175 et seq.) under Subtitle 3;
Building Code under Subtitle 4, Division 1;
Fire Prevention Code under Subtitle 11, Division 4;
Pest control provisions under Subtitle 12, Division 5;
Housing Code, property standards and maintenance, and antilitter and weed ordinance, under Subtitle 13, Divisions 1, 7, and 9, respectively;
Sewage disposal nuisances under Subtitle 22, Division 3, Subdivision 3; and
Abandoned vehicles under Subtitle 26, Division 14.

The notice shall specify:
The nature of the alleged nuisance;
The date and time of day the nuisance was first discovered;
The location on the property where the nuisance is allegedly occurring; and
The relief sought.
